## Overview
Add keyboard shortcuts for quick source filter manipulation.

## Keybinding: F11 for Source Filter
Following the existing F-key pattern (F3/F4 for other filters), use F11 for source filtering:

```rust
// In key handling
KeyCode::F(11) => {
    // F11: Cycle source filter
    self.cycle_source_filter();
}
```

This aligns with the document's suggestion to maintain F-key consistency.

### Filter Cycling Logic
```rust
fn cycle_source_filter(&mut self) {
    self.source_filter = match &self.source_filter {
        SourceFilter::All => SourceFilter::Local,
        SourceFilter::Local => SourceFilter::Remote,
        SourceFilter::Remote => {
            if let Some(first_host) = self.available_sources.first() {
                SourceFilter::Hostname(first_host.clone())
            } else {
                SourceFilter::All
            }
        }
        SourceFilter::Hostname(current) => {
            let idx = self.available_sources.iter()
                .position(|h| h == current)
                .map(|i| i + 1)
                .unwrap_or(0);
            if idx < self.available_sources.len() {
                SourceFilter::Hostname(self.available_sources[idx].clone())
            } else {
                SourceFilter::All
            }
        }
    };
    self.apply_source_filter();
}
```

